Listing.create(:id => 2, :title => "iphone 5", :description => "The iPhone 5 is a touchscreen-based smartphone developed by Apple Inc.. It is the sixth generation of the iPhone and succeeds the iPhone 4S. The phone is a slimmer, lighter model that introduces a higher-resolution, 4-inch screen to the series with 16:9 widescreen aspect ratio. The phone also includes a custom-designed ARMv7 processor called the Apple A6, an update to Apple's mobile operating system known as iOS 6, and support for LTE.", :starting_price => 1, :current_price => 1, :rrp => 40000, :start_date => "Fri, 09 Aug 2013 10:01:13 UTC +00:00", :duration => 86400, :time_per_bid => 1, :default_end_date => "Sat, 10 Aug 2013 10:01:13 UTC +00:00", :active => true, :photo_file_name => "iphone-5S.jpg", :photo_content_type => "image/jpeg", :photo_file_size => 61575, :photo_updated_at => "Mon, 12 Aug 2013 19:33:52 UTC +00:00")
Listing.create(:id => 4, :title => "PS3", :description => "The list of games for the PlayStation®3 system is growing daily. The PS3™ system delivers the goods from some of the industry's hottest franchises, like SOCOM, to the most anticipated games of the year, like God of War® III. Whatever you want to play, chances are the PS3™ game library has it.", :starting_price => 1, :current_price => 1, :rrp => 300, :start_date => "Fri, 09 Aug 2013 10:27:57 UTC +00:00", :duration => 86400, :time_per_bid => 1, :default_end_date => "Sat, 10 Aug 2013 10:27:57 UTC +00:00", :active => true, :photo_file_name => "gold-ps3.jpg", :photo_content_type => "image/jpeg", :photo_file_size => 106266, :photo_updated_at => "Mon, 12 Aug 2013 19:33:58 UTC +00:00")
Listing.create(:id => 3, :title => "Nintendo Wii U", :description => "Discover a wealth of exciting new ways to enjoy home entertainment with Wii U, Nintendo's next home console. With a revolutionary new touch screen controller, precision motion controls, and full HD graphics, a whole new world of play styles and gaming possibilities is on the horizon. The time is coming to truly expand your idea about what a game console is - and can be. The Premium Pack includes the 32GB Wii U console, the amazing new GamePad controller, the Nintendo Land game and more.According to Nintendo President Satoru Iwata, \"Wii U redefines the structure of home entertainment by fundamentally changing how the TV, the game console and the Internet function and interact together,\" he continues, \"The experience enabled by Wii U and its new controller takes players deeper into their games, while reaching out wider than ever before to be inviting to all kinds of gamers.\"Wii U combines motion-sensing gameplay with the ability to support full HD graphics. Each Wii U console will be paired with a new groundbreaking controller, with its 6.2-inch wide screen. Previously, video games played on a home consoles have been confined to the TV and offered identical viewpoints to each player in a multiplayer environment. The Wii U controller enhances that experience with different viewpoints available in-game and in differing games/game situations. Also, watching TV and playing console games have been completely separate experiences. The new controller removes these boundaries, creating a more dynamic and fluid gaming and entertainment experience.", :starting_price => 1, :current_price => 1, :rrp => 30000, :start_date => "Fri, 09 Aug 2013 10:27:43 UTC +00:00", :duration => 86400, :time_per_bid => 10, :default_end_date => "Sat, 10 Aug 2013 10:27:43 UTC +00:00", :active => true, :photo_file_name => "Wii_U_console_and_controller.png", :photo_content_type => "image/png", :photo_file_size => 366739, :photo_updated_at => "Mon, 12 Aug 2013 19:33:55 UTC +00:00")
Listing.create(:id => 5, :title => "bugatti veyron", :description => "The Bugatti Veyron EB 16.4 is a mid-engined grand touring car, designed and developed by the Volkswagen Group and manufactured in Molsheim, France by Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S.\r\nThe Super Sport version of the Veyron is the fastest street-legal production car in the world, with a top speed of 431.072 km/h (267.856 mph).[4] The original version has a top speed of 408.47 km/h (253.81 mph).[5] It was named Car of the Decade (2000–2009) by the BBC television programme Top Gear. The standard Bugatti Veyron won Top Gear's Best Car Driven All Year award in 2005.", :starting_price => 1, :current_price => 1, :rrp => 200000000, :start_date => "Fri, 09 Aug 2013 10:29:02 UTC +00:00", :duration => 86400, :time_per_bid => 20, :default_end_date => "Sat, 10 Aug 2013 10:29:02 UTC +00:00", :active => true, :photo_file_name => "Bugatti_Veyron_16.4_–_Frontansicht_(1)__5._April_2012__Düsseldorf.jpg", :photo_content_type => "image/jpeg", :photo_file_size => 95178, :photo_updated_at => "Mon, 12 Aug 2013 19:34:00 UTC +00:00")
Listing.create(:id => 6, :title => "Macbook Air", :description => "The 11-inch MacBook Air now lasts up to 9 hours between charges and the 13-inch model lasts up to an incredible 12 hours. So from your morning coffee till your evening commute, you can work unplugged. When it’s time to kick back and relax, you can get up to 8 hours of iTunes film playback on the 11-inch model and up to 10 hours on the 13-inch model. And with up to 30 days of standby time, you can go away for weeks and pick up where you left off.", :starting_price => 1, :current_price => 1, :rrp => 100000, :start_date => "Fri, 09 Aug 2013 10:29:13 UTC +00:00", :duration => 86400, :time_per_bid => 10, :default_end_date => "Sat, 10 Aug 2013 10:29:13 UTC +00:00", :active => true, :photo_file_name => "apple-12q2-macbook-air-13-front-lg.jpg", :photo_content_type => "image/jpeg", :photo_file_size => 157315, :photo_updated_at => "Mon, 12 Aug 2013 19:34:02 UTC +00:00")
Listing.create(:id => 7, :title => "Nexus 10", :description => "With a dazzling 2560x1600 (300 ppi) display and ultra-powerful graphics processor, Nexus 10 places you right inside the action with picture-perfect performance. Over 4 million pixels in your hands means that text is sharper, HD movies are more vivid and photos come to life in stunning detail.\r\n", :starting_price => 1, :current_price => 1, :rrp => 20000, :start_date => "Fri, 09 Aug 2013 10:32:09 UTC +00:00", :duration => 86400, :time_per_bid => 10, :default_end_date => "Sat, 10 Aug 2013 10:32:09 UTC +00:00", :active => false, :photo_file_name => "n10-product-hero.png", :photo_content_type => "image/png", :photo_file_size => 343878, :photo_updated_at => "Mon, 12 Aug 2013 19:34:05 UTC +00:00")
Listing.create(:id => 8, :title => "Typhoon", :description => "The Eurofighter Typhoon is a twin-engine, canard-delta wing, multirole fighter.[6][7] The Typhoon was designed and is manufactured by a consortium of three companies; EADS, Alenia Aeronautica and BAE Systems, who conduct the majority of affairs dealing with the project through a joint holding company, Eurofighter Jagdflugzeug GmbH, which was formed in 1986. The project is managed by the NATO Eurofighter and Tornado Management Agency, which also acts as the prime customer.[8]\r\nDevelopment of the aircraft effectively began in 1983 with the Future European Fighter Aircraft programme, a multinational collaborative effort between Germany, France, UK, Italy and Spain. Due to disagreements over design authority and operational requirements, France left the consortium to independently develop the Dassault Rafale instead. A technology demonstration aircraft, the British Aerospace EAP, first took flight on 6 August 1986; the first prototype of the finalised Eurofighter made its first flight on 27 March 1994. The name of the aircraft, Typhoon, was formally adopted in September 1998; the first production contracts were signed that same year.", :starting_price => 1, :current_price => 1, :rrp => 2400000, :start_date => "Fri, 09 Aug 2013 10:33:35 UTC +00:00", :duration => 86400, :time_per_bid => 30, :default_end_date => "Sat, 10 Aug 2013 10:33:35 UTC +00:00", :active => true, :photo_file_name => "Typhoon.jpg", :photo_content_type => "image/jpeg", :photo_file_size => 316728, :photo_updated_at => "Mon, 12 Aug 2013 19:34:08 UTC +00:00")

